Program: Omnibus
Title: The Flight of Tiny Feet
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mlk
Last Broadcast Date: 14 February 2003
After the Japanese invasion of Burma in 1942, thousands of British and Indian refugees embarked on a hazardous 1000-mile trek to India. Survivors Stephen Brookes, Evan Edwardes and Yolande Rodda, recall their harrowing childhood experience.